# Real Time Clock (RTC) Display Alarm Clock


## Project Overview

The Real Time Clock (RTC) Display Alarm Clock is an embedded systems project developed using Arduino/ESP32 and a 4-digit 7-segment display. The system is designed to display the current time in real time and provide alarm clock functionality. Users can easily adjust the current time, set alarm timings, enable or disable alarms, and use the snooze feature when the alarm is triggered.

This project demonstrates the integration of RTC-based timekeeping, user input through push buttons, display interfacing, and alarm management in an embedded environment.

## Objectives

* To display real-time hours and minutes using a 7-segment display.
* To implement alarm clock functionality.
* To provide an easy-to-use interface for setting time and alarms.
* To generate an audible alert when the alarm time is reached.
* To demonstrate practical applications of Embedded Systems and IoT concepts.

## Features

* Real-Time Clock (RTC) Display
* Time Adjustment Using Push Buttons
* Alarm Enable/Disable Function
* Alarm Time Configuration
* Snooze Functionality
* Audible Alarm Notification Using Buzzer
* User-Friendly Operation

## Components Used

* ESP32 / Arduino Board
* RTC Module (DS1307/DS3231)
* 4-Digit 7-Segment Display
* Push Buttons
* Buzzer/Speaker
* Jumper Wires
* Breadboard

## Working Principle

The RTC module continuously maintains accurate time. The current time is displayed on the 4-digit 7-segment display. Users can modify the current time and configure alarm settings using dedicated buttons. When the current time matches the preset alarm time, the buzzer generates an alarm tone. The user can either stop the alarm or activate the snooze feature.

## Repository Contents

* Source Code Files
* Header Files and Configuration Files
* Circuit Design (`diagram.json`)
* Output Screenshot (`output.png`)
* Project Documentation (`README.md`)

## Output

The project successfully displays real-time clock information and provides alarm functionality with snooze support. The system serves as a compact and efficient digital alarm clock suitable for educational and embedded systems learning purposes.

## Conclusion

This project provides hands-on experience in RTC interfacing, display control, button handling, and alarm management. It demonstrates the practical implementation of embedded systems concepts and can be extended further with additional smart clock features.

